description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Advert for Band 5 posts - The Neonatal Service&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We are looking for enthusiastic and motivated Band 5 Staff Nurses to join the Level 3 Neonatal Service team at Bradford Teaching Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust. Accredited as the first NICU in the country with UNICEF Baby Friendly Neonatal Standards we are very proud of the parents as partners in care ethos that underpins every aspect of the care we deliver to babies and their families within the service. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For successful applicants we are committed to offer a comprehensive competency based education package with support to develop and access continuing professional development. In addition you will have the opportunity to be involved in quality improvement initiatives within your team. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;No previous neonatal nursing experience necessary.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Neonatal Service at Bradford Teaching Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust is a friendly, innovative and forward thinking multi-disciplinary team that provides high quality care for babies from across the Yorkshire and Humber and beyond. We are proud of our close relationships with other neonatal units in the Yorkshire and Humber Operational Delivery Network and with Embrace. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Get in touch to find out more:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ward Manager Julie Pearce on 01274 364522 or Julie.pearce@bthft.nhs.uk&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
